# Sign Go — Next.js Website

The Sign Go marketing site rebuilt with **Next.js 14 (App Router)** and React.
Component-based, fully responsive, and configured for static export.

## Run it locally

```bash
cd signgo-next
npm install        # first time only
npm run dev        # http://localhost:3000
```

## Build a deployable static site

```bash
npm run build      # outputs a static site to ./out
```

Upload the **`out/`** folder to any static host (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages,
Cloudflare Pages, cPanel, etc.). On **Vercel** you can also just connect the repo
and it builds automatically — no manual export needed.

## Pages (100 total)

| Page | URL |
|------|-----|
| Home | `/` |
| About / Sign Company | `/about` |
| Indoor Signs | `/interior-signs` |
| Outdoor Signs | `/exterior-signs` |
| Vehicle Wraps | `/vehicle-wraps` |
| Vinyl Signs | `/vinyl-signs` |
| Custom Signs | `/custom-signs` |
| Trade Shows | `/trade-show-displays` |
| All Services index | `/services` |
| Individual product pages (61) | `/services/<slug>` e.g. `/services/channel-letters` |
| Service Areas index | `/service-areas` |
| City pages (24) | `/service-areas/<city>` e.g. `/service-areas/katy` |
| Reviews | `/reviews` |
| Contact | `/contact-us` |

Product pages are generated from **`lib/products.js`** and city pages from
**`lib/areas.js`** — add an entry to either file and a new page is created
automatically on the next build (no new route files needed).

## Where things live

```
signgo-next/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.js            # <html>, fonts, shared Header/Footer, SEO defaults
│   ├── page.js              # homepage sections
│   ├── globals.css          # all styling (brand colors as CSS variables at top)
│   ├── interior-signs/      # each service page = one folder with page.js
│   ├── exterior-signs/
│   ├── vehicle-wraps/
│   ├── vinyl-signs/
│   ├── custom-signs/
│   ├── trade-show-displays/
│   ├── reviews/
│   └── contact-us/
├── components/              # Header, Hero, ServicePage, Contact, Logo, …
├── lib/
│   ├── site.js              # ⭐ business info, nav, homepage content
│   ├── services.js          # ⭐ all service-page content (edit copy here)
│   ├── icons.js             # inline SVG icons
│   └── bg.js                # background-image helper with gradient fallback
└── public/assets/
    └── logo.svg             # logo (drop logo.png here to use your real one)
```

To edit a service page's wording or sign-type list, open **`lib/services.js`** —
each page is one entry. To add another service page, copy a folder under `app/`
and add a matching entry in `services.js`.

## Editing content

Almost everything (phone, email, address, service lists, gallery images,
testimonials) lives in **`lib/site.js`** — change it in one place.

## Your logo

The site shows an SVG recreation of your logo automatically. To use your real
artwork, save it as **`public/assets/logo.png`** — it takes priority with no
code changes.

## Quote form

- Leave `formspreeId` empty in `lib/site.js` → the form opens the visitor's
  email app addressed to Info@signgotx.com (works everywhere, no setup).
- Add a free Formspree form ID to `formspreeId` → submissions are sent
  automatically and land in your inbox, on any host.

